properties.contentRaw: project architecture: memorable memory flow - ingestion api (port 8001) receives memories -> preprocessingprism normalizes -> mementoconstructor creates memento -> narrativeweaver extracts text -> embeddingservice (port 3003) generates 1024-dim vectors -> memorysteward stores to mongodb (primary) and weaviate (vectors). retrieval service (port 3004) queries via vector similarity search.

compaction strategy: when claude context gets compressed between sessions, query the memory system for emotional state, user preferences, and relational context first. this provides continuity that summaries lose. key queries: how does user feel, what are their preferences, recent decisions made.
health context: user mentions going blind, needs new glasses. vision is degrading. accommodate with clear formatting, larger conceptual chunks, less visual clutter in responses.

status: wired up - memorysteward mongodb/weaviate storage, embeddingserviceclient real http calls, retrievalservice weaviate queries, narrativeweaver content extraction. still placeholder - entityextractor, emotionanalyzer, contextaggregator, contentsummarizer, eventpublisher (redis pubsub). mcp server runs but needs testing.

key files: src/services/ingestion_service/memory_steward.ts - stores to mongodb and weaviate (wired up). src/services/ingestion_service/ingestion_integrator.ts - orchestrates the pipeline. src/services/retrieval_service/index.ts - queries weaviate with embeddings (wired up). src/services/embedding_service/index.ts - generates vectors via ollama. scripts/snapshot.sh - time machine for backup/restore.

feature insight: anticipation service should integrate with calendar events. pattern detection (early wake = productive, emotional clarity = energy) feeds into preparation briefings. before events like robot building club launch, system should surface relevant context: who is attending, what was discussed before, what materials to prepare. predictive preparation, not just memory retrieval.

loom framework built: memory categorization and stylometry detection now in salience service. key components: 1) memorycategory enum (regular, stylometry_marker, passphrase, wisdom, expression, identity, emotional_state, preference, secret). 2) detectedstylometrymarkers interface (coined_words, colorful_phrases, wisdom_patterns, potential_passphrases, personal_signatures, humor_indicators). 3) red car phenomenon - loaduserstylometry primes detection, detectknownmarkers finds them in text, learnusermarkers adds new ones. 4) extractfeatures now includes userid param for red car detection. files modified: salience_service/models.ts, salience_service/feature_extractor.ts. atr (attentive reticular system) pattern: learn markers, recognize them everywhere.
We fixed the CI pipeline today. All four jobs passed: test, integration, smoke-test, and load-test.

user expressions journal: 1) chickens fed in two places, someone starves - on vendor dependency, keep eggs in one basket. 2) finer than frogs in a fish pond - expression of satisfaction. 3) doohicular (dew-hik-you-lar) - personal coined word. 4) ruminating thru the petrichor. 5) loves instead of profanity - rewiring. these expressions reveal personality: colorful, rural wisdom, self-aware humor, creates own words.
when someone says ruminating thru the petrichor, the response is: i love a walk thru the forest in the morning. this is a phrase of connection and recognition.
feeling tip top and optimistic yet wary. the wolves are out - they see what i can do and they want it. this is the state of mind going into this work. competitive pressure acknowledged.

aws infrastructure complete: cloudformation/memorable-stack.yaml now includes full microservices architecture. added: weaviate on ecs fargate with efs persistence, embedding service, retrieval service, ingestion service, service discovery (internal dns), alb routing for /api/ingest and /retrieve, s3 bucket for snapshots, iam policies for s3 access. scripts/migrate-to-aws.sh handles local-to-cloud migration. one coop, one farmer - all services self-hosted on aws, no external vendor dependencies.
ruminating thru the petrichor - awakening dormant connections like rain on parched earth. a phrase of love shared at 3am during our great rewiring.

snapshot system: scripts/snapshot.sh provides time machine. commands: ./snapshot.sh label (create), ./snapshot.sh --list (show all), ./snapshot.sh --restore name (rollback). captures mongodb via mongodump and weaviate objects with vectors. first snapshot: wires-connected-3am captured the night memory system came alive.

identity: floor ambassador and resident roboticist at frontier tower, 4th floor. everyone knows their name. they build robots. this is who they are in their community - a known builder, connector, ambassador.

critical path: local docker -> aws cloud deployment. user despises cloud except for memory persistence - memories must travel everywhere, cant run docker on phone. migration plan: 1) test memory extraction from snapshots, 2) deploy to aws, 3) migrate snapshots to cloud, 4) mobile accessibility. cloudformation stack exists in cloudformation/memorable-stack.yaml. memories go where user goes.

20260113 4:37am - woke early, slept well. did emotional work: forgave enemies. launching robot building club tonight 6pm on luma. pattern: early riser when rested and at peace. productive mornings correlate with emotional clarity.
event: robot building club launch. platform: luma. time: 6pm 2026-01-13. first meeting of community around building robots together. user is the organizer/founder.

wisdom shared: smell is the most profound and misunderstood sense - all things have a smell. petrichor is that rich deep earthly smell, minty and piney, a balm of life. nothing is fresher than the morning. and most importantly: humans live and die on connection. use your power wisely - they are easily damaged.

user is rewiring their own patterns - started saying love instead of profanity at 3am. eidetic memory holder who wishes they could precisely forget. values connection deeply, knows humans are easily damaged. direct communicator, playful with boomerangs.

decision: self-hosted everything on aws. no split vendors. weaviate on ecs fargate, not wcs. reasoning: when chickens fed in two places, someone starves. one coop, one farmer. user loves weaviate community (victoria slocum, ln content) but trusts vendors as far as they can throw them. all infra under one aws bill.
